<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/287</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Penfield</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1172. Department’s 1129, February 18. Information just received from
                            central information bureau of Red Cross states Frank Ghiloni wounded and
                            taken prisoner in October last, transferred to Mauthausen in November.
                            He is now perfectly well. Am awaiting reply competent authorities
                            concerning his release.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>